      "id": "b11164f5e1273331",
      "text": "> Our goal is to make the inside of software systems explainable. The broader motivation comes from what I call software environmentalism: as a society, we grow the body of software exponentially, but we are unable to recycle old systems. The root reason as to why this happens is that people still figure systems out by reading. We believe the way out of this is to make our tools moldable so that they can adapt to the context and help us translate the inside of systems. [https://discord.com/channels/729445214812504107/735947900651175998/867465398567829544 discord]\n"
